The '''mountain thornbill''' ('''''Acanthiza katherina''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Acanthizidae]]. It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Australia]].

Its natural [[habitat]] is tropical [[rainforest]] on the [[Atherton Tableland]] in north-east Queensland.

